results.locality: Saltwater Creek, Maryborough, A relatively small tidal creek about five kilometres in length between the Mary River and the Bruce Highway. The vegetation to the south of the creek has been extensively cleared for sugar cane leaving a narrow riparian corridor that includes small degraded patches of vine scrub and mangroves. The vegetation to the north of the creek is largely intact. Public access is via a number of road reserves, a couple with bridges.

Redbank Ck crossing, Adare Road, Gatton, Around Redbank Creek banks. Eucalypts, Acacia, Casuarina and Chinese Elms  with understory of lantana and long grass. Survey along road and public areas of creek banks
Narooma 10' Cell, Narooma and surrounding district including forests and beaches, including Lake Corunna. Extends from south Dalmeny in the north to Tilba Tilba in the south.
Shorncliffe, Established bayside suburb with tidal mudflats at the mouth of Cabbage Tree Creek. Mangroves along the creek and some freshwater ponds on Sandgate golf course.

Helidon Spa, nr Helidon, Small housing estate with two man-made ponds for recycliing; one, the more western of the two, is predominantly fresh water, whilst the other back to the east is saline. Access off Warrego Hwy

Walter Zimmerman Park, Pine Mountain, Dry Sclerophyll woodland (E moluccana - Gum-topped box). Ipswich City Council park and surrounds, including old Fernvale railway line. Access from Walter Zimmerman Park car park in Kirkston Place.

Warriewood Wetlands, The Warriewood Wetland comprises approximately 30.5 hectares including Irrawong Reserve, and is zoned 7A, Environmental Protection. The remnant forest in the wetland and Irrawong Reserve is part of the last significant stand of swamp mahogany forest in Sydney.
Lake Mitchell (Quaids Dam), Wetlands with fringing woodland. Access through gate onto causeway.

Bowling Green Bay NP (Alligator Creek), A great little section of the Bowling Green Bay National park, 24km SE of Townsville City; Take care when swimming. Camping area under redevelopment (2011).  Good Picnic and Day Use area, good walks, good birding.

Adare Road Lagoon, nr Gatton, Large farm dam just to the west off Adare Road, which runs north of Gatton; dead trees and various aquatic vegetation within; surrounded by temperate eucalypt woodland and some acacia scrub.
Jervis Bay National Park (Huskisson), Section of Jervis Bay National Park that lies adjacent to Huskisson.
Orange 10' Cell, Great Dividing Range: town, botanical gardens, surrounding farmlands, dams, parks and gardens.
Lumo Conservancy  plus  Taita Wildlife Sanctuary

Toorbul 10' Cell, Includes Toorbul, Donnybrook, Sandstone Point, Godwin Beach, Ningi, Beachmere on the mainland and Welsby, Banksia Beach, Bellara, Bongaree and Buckley's Hole on Bribie Island. Also includes Deception Bay waters associated with Caboolture River Estuary.
Anstead Bushland Reserve, Mainly Eucalypt woodland, with some open areas and a border on the Brisbane river.  Open access, with car park on Hawkesbury Road.
Dowse Lagoon, Sandgate, Rehabilitated Freshwater lagoon. Access off Keogh St.
